DUBLIN (Reuters) - Ireland's government was on a knife-edge on Tuesday with damaged Prime Minister Brian Cowen challenging the opposition to let an austerity budget pass and trigger an EU/IMF bailout before early elections.&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
&lt;a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?a=1g9h3e7FuzE:hHit5HTz18U:yIl2AUoC8zA"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?a=1g9h3e7FuzE:hHit5HTz18U:F7zBnMyn0Lo"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?i=1g9h3e7FuzE:hHit5HTz18U:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?a=1g9h3e7FuzE:hHit5HTz18U:V_sGLiPBpWU"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?i=1g9h3e7FuzE:hHit5HTz18U:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/reuters/worldNews/~4/1g9h3e7FuzE" height="1" width="1"/&gt;

GREYMOUTH, New Zealand (Reuters) - Hopes of finding 29 men trapped in a New Zealand mine alive were rapidly fading on Tuesday, with footage of the blast at the mine four days ago showing debris flung out of the shaft like a bullet from a gun.&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
&lt;a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?a=CGXVwpVT5Xw:0QGFmdUxc88:yIl2AUoC8zA"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?a=CGXVwpVT5Xw:0QGFmdUxc88:F7zBnMyn0Lo"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?i=CGXVwpVT5Xw:0QGFmdUxc88:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?a=CGXVwpVT5Xw:0QGFmdUxc88:V_sGLiPBpWU"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?i=CGXVwpVT5Xw:0QGFmdUxc88:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
