INCHEON, South Korea (Reuters) - North Korea on Tuesday fired dozens of artillery shells at a South Korean island, killing two soldiers and setting houses ablaze, in one of the heaviest attacks on its neighbor since the Korean War ended in 1953.&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
&lt;a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?a=2D8tfLs9s-E:Zeqx8rbPBko:yIl2AUoC8zA"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?a=2D8tfLs9s-E:Zeqx8rbPBko:F7zBnMyn0Lo"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?i=2D8tfLs9s-E:Zeqx8rbPBko:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?a=2D8tfLs9s-E:Zeqx8rbPBko:V_sGLiPBpWU"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/reuters/worldNews?i=2D8tfLs9s-E:Zeqx8rbPBko:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
